{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_374ad6f30c1344458190ac71","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t# Huxley\n2\tHuxley is a web application designed to manage the annual [Berkeley Model United Nations](http://bmun.org/) conference.\n3\t\n4\t[![Build Status](https://travis-ci.org/bmun/huxley.svg?branch=master)](https://travis-ci.org/bmun/huxley)\n5\t[![styled with prettier](https://img.shields.io/badge/styled_with-prettier-ff69b4.svg)](https://github.com/prettier/prettier)\n6\t\n7\t\n8\t## About BMUN\n9\tThe Berkeley Model United Nations conference is a high-school conference hosted every spring. Each year, we host over 1500 delegates from all over the country (and the world!), who compete in a simulation of the United Nations and other international/historical bodies to solve the world's most compelling problems.\n10\t\n11\t## About Huxley\n12\tOur long-term vision is to make Huxley the **best Model UN software in the world**: an application that makes the conference experience smoother than it's ever been for advisors and secretariats. We want Huxley to be **delightful to use**, and we're aiming to provide a fantastic user experience via a focus on clear UI and thoughtful, easy-to-use features.\n13\t\n14\tHuxley's built with [Django](http://www.djangoproject.com), with a frontend written in [React](http://facebook.github.io/react/).\n15\t\n16\t## Contribute\n17\tWe'd love for you to contribute to Huxley! Discover how to set up Huxley locally and submit patches in [**CONTRIBUTING.md**](CONTRIBUTING.md).\n18\t\n19\t### License\n20\tUse of this source code is governed by a BSD License found in [`LICENSE`](LICENSE).\n21\t"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"57c0b579-c617-43af-a22b-565dc946c318","uuid":"b322d681-6e3d-4c40-bbd0-96d40d01b8cc","timestamp":"2026-04-08T21:38:08.119Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/workspace/README.md","content":"# Huxley\nHuxley is a web application designed to manage the annual [Berkeley Model United Nations](http://bmun.org/) conference.\n\n[![Build Status](https://travis-ci.org/bmun/huxley.svg?branch=master)](https://travis-ci.org/bmun/huxley)\n[![styled with prettier](https://img.shields.io/badge/styled_with-prettier-ff69b4.svg)](https://github.com/prettier/prettier)\n\n\n## About BMUN\nThe Berkeley Model United Nations conference is a high-school conference hosted every spring. Each year, we host over 1500 delegates from all over the country (and the world!), who compete in a simulation of the United Nations and other international/historical bodies to solve the world's most compelling problems.\n\n## About Huxley\nOur long-term vision is to make Huxley the **best Model UN software in the world**: an application that makes the conference experience smoother than it's ever been for advisors and secretariats. We want Huxley to be **delightful to use**, and we're aiming to provide a fantastic user experience via a focus on clear UI and thoughtful, easy-to-use features.\n\nHuxley's built with [Django](http://www.djangoproject.com), with a frontend written in [React](http://facebook.github.io/react/).\n\n## Contribute\nWe'd love for you to contribute to Huxley! Discover how to set up Huxley locally and submit patches in [**CONTRIBUTING.md**](CONTRIBUTING.md).\n\n### License\nUse of this source code is governed by a BSD License found in [`LICENSE`](LICENSE).\n","numLines":21,"startLine":1,"totalLines":21}}}
